        <img class="img" src="./Tirunelveli railway img.jpeg" />
        <p class="p">ABOUT DISTRICT
            Tirunelveli also known as Nellai and historically as Tinnevelly, is a major district in the Indian state of
            Tamil Nadu. Tirunelveli city is the administrative headquarters of the <span>Tirunelveli District</span>.
            Tirunelveli
            Municipal Corporation is the sixth-largest municipal corporation in the state of Tamil Nadu</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"> <i class="material-icons">	&#xe561;</i>
        <h3 class="h3">Halwa</h3>
        <img class="img" src="./tirunelveli-halwa.jpg" />
        <p class="p">
            Tirunelveli halwa is known for its unique texture and flavor. The dish is very popular in Tamil Nadu and is
            often served at weddings and other special occasions. The health benefits of Tirunelveli halwa are numerous.
            The dish is rich in vitamins and minerals, and it is also a good source of fiber.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"><i class="material-icons">&#xeb48;</i>
        <h3>Courtallam</h3><img class="img" src="./Courtallam_Falls.jpg" />
        <p class="p">The panchayat town of Tirunelveli district is home to the beautiful Courtallam Waterfalls. The
            waterfall's
            520-foot drop means you can take in its full majesty. The large, pleasant hills and verdant landscape will
            capture your attention.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"><i class="material-icons">&#xe8b4;</i>
        <h3>Agasthiyar Falls</h3><img class="img" src="./Tirunelveli_agasthiyar Falls.jpg" />
        <p class="p">
            Anyone who bathes in the waters of Agasthiyar Falls, a beautiful cascade, is said to be cleansed of their
            sins. Just 42 kilometres from Tirunelveli, on the Tamiraparani River, lies the stunning Agasthiyar Falls.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"><i class="material-icons">&#xe564;</i>
        <h3>Papanasam Dam</h3><img class="img" src="./papanasam Dam.JPG 3.jpg" />
        <p class="p">
            Papanasam, a little village, is one of the most visited places in Tirunelveli due to its peaceful atmosphere
            and beautiful sights. Located 37 kilometres from Tirunelveli, Papanasam is most well-known as the site of
            the Papanasam Temple, dedicated to a deity widely believed to be an avatar of Lord Shiva.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"><i class="material-icons">&#xe32a;</i>
        <p>
        <h3>Kalakkadu</h3><img class="img" src="./kalakad.JPG" />
        <p class="p">Tirunelveli's Kalakkadu Wildlife Sanctuary is a popular tourist destination
            since it's one of the few spots
            in all of South India where tigers are safely protected from poachers. Besides the lion-tailed macaque,
            Nilgiri langur, Nilgiri tahr, sambar, panther, wild dog, and pangolin will all make appearances for your
            viewing pleasure</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <i class="material-icons">&#xe6e1;</i>
        <h3>Manjolai</h3><img class="img" src="./majolai.jpg" />
        <p class="p">Beautiful Manjolai can be found in the Kalakad Mundanthurai Tiger ReserveManjolai is a small hill
            station
            situated at an altitude of 1162 m in Tirunelveli district of Tamilnadu. It is located at a distance of 23 km
            from Manimuthar and 63 from Tirunelveli..</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card"><i class="material-icons">&#xeb4c;</i>
